---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const lastUpdated = "March 29, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Draigon Idle — how we collect, use, and protect your data."
>
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="privacy-title">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="section-title" id="privacy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="section-body">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>

      <div class="legal-content">
        <p>
          Stonemill Studios ("<strong>we</strong>," "<strong>us</strong>," or
          "<strong>our</strong>") operates the Draigon Idle mobile game
          (the "<strong>Game</strong>") and the website draigonidle.com
          (the "<strong>Site</strong>"). This Privacy Policy explains what
          information we collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>Automatically Collected Data</h3>
        <p>
          When you play the Game, Firebase Analytics automatically collects
          certain usage data, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Device type, operating system, and app version</li>
          <li>In-game events and session duration</li>
          <li>Crash reports and performance diagnostics</li>
          <li>General geographic region (country-level)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data is collected in aggregate and used solely to improve the
          Game. We do not use it to build individual advertising profiles.
        </p>

        <h3>Cloud Save Data</h3>
        <p>
          If you opt in to cloud saves, your game progress is stored in
          Firebase Firestore. This includes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Guild state, outpost levels, and quest progress</li>
          <li>Companion roster and upgrade history</li>
          <li>In-game settings and preferences</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Cloud saves are linked to an anonymous account identifier. We do
          not associate save data with your name, email, or any other
          personally identifying information unless you explicitly provide it.
        </p>

        <h3>Local Storage</h3>
        <p>
          Game progress is also stored locally on your device using the Isar
          database. This data never leaves your device unless you enable cloud
          saves.
        </p>

        <h3>Newsletter Sign-Up</h3>
        <p>
          If you subscribe to our mailing list via the Site, your email
          address is collected and stored by Kit (formerly ConvertKit). We
          use your email address only to send you updates about Draigon Idle.
          You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in any email we send.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To operate and improve the Game and Site</li>
          <li>To diagnose crashes and fix technical issues</li>
          <li>To sync your game progress across devices (if cloud saves are enabled)</li>
          <li>To send you news and updates about the Game (newsletter subscribers only)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          Draigon Idle uses the following third-party services. Each service
          operates under its own privacy policy:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Firebase</strong> — analytics, crash reporting, and
            cloud saves.
            <a
              href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Firebase Privacy Policy</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Kit (ConvertKit)</strong> — email newsletter management.
            <a
              href="https://kit.com/privacy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Kit Privacy Policy</a>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Draigon Idle is not directed to children under the age of 13. We do
          not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
          If you believe a child under 13 has provided us with personal
          information, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:privacy@stonemillstudios.com">privacy@stonemillstudios.com</a>
          and we will delete it promptly.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you are located in a jurisdiction with stricter age requirements
          (such as the EEA, where the applicable age may be up to 16), the
          same principle applies.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          Analytics data is retained per Google Firebase's default retention
          settings. Cloud save data is retained for the lifetime of your
          anonymous account. Newsletter subscriber data is retained until you
          unsubscribe. You may request deletion of your data at any time by
          contacting us.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct,
          or delete the personal information we hold about you. To exercise
          these rights, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:privacy@stonemillstudios.com">privacy@stonemillstudios.com</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we
          will revise the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We
          encourage you to review this page periodically.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, contact
          us at:
        </p>
        <address>
          Stonemill Studios<br />
          <a href="mailto:privacy@stonemillstudios.com">privacy@stonemillstudios.com</a>
        </address>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-content {
    margin-top: var(--space-8);
    max-width: 72ch;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .legal-content > * + * {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: var(--space-10);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .legal-content h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
  }

  .legal-content ul li + li {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .legal-content address {
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }

  .legal-content strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
  }
</style>
